p:\mathbb R\to S^1
p(t)=e^{2\pi ti}
\phi:\mathbb R\to \mathbb R
p(\phi(t))=p(t)
t\in \mathbb R
e^{2\pi i\phi(t)}=e^{2\pi it} \implies cos(2\pi\phi(t))+isin(2\pi\phi(t))=  cos(2\pi t)+isin(2\pi t)
\implies cos(2\pi\phi(t))=cos(2\pi t)
sin(2\pi\phi(t))=sin(2\pi t)
\phi(t)=kt
k\in \mathbb Z
